From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Keyur Maru <kd2maru@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 05:28:29 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] libmeminfo: don't abort when the gpuMem BPF map is absent

The gpuMem BPF program hangs off the gpu_mem/gpu_mem_total tracepoint, which the
4.9 kernel channel runs does not have, so bpfloader never loads the program and
never pins map_gpuMem_gpu_mem_total_map. The BpfMapRO(pathname) constructor
aborts on a missing map, and system_server reads this map from AMS' AppProfiler,
so the missing tracepoint takes down system_server.

Probe the pin with access() before opening it and degrade gracefully: report no
per-process GPU memory rather than crashing. On a kernel that does have the
tracepoint this is one extra stat() and nothing else changes.
---
 sysmeminfo.cpp | 14 ++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+)

diff --git a/sysmeminfo.cpp b/sysmeminfo.cpp
index c014987..8d36952 100644
--- a/sysmeminfo.cpp
+++ b/sysmeminfo.cpp
@@ -415,6 +415,13 @@ bool ReadPerProcessGpuMem([[maybe_unused]] std::unordered_map<uint32_t, uint64_t
 #if defined(__ANDROID__) && !defined(__ANDROID_APEX__) && !defined(__ANDROID_VNDK__)
     static constexpr const char kBpfGpuMemTotalMap[] = "/sys/fs/bpf/map_gpuMem_gpu_mem_total_map";
 
+    // channel A17: the gpuMem eBPF program relies on the gpu_mem/gpu_mem_total tracepoint, which
+    // this 4.9 kernel does not have, so bpfloader never pins the map. The BpfMapRO(pathname)
+    // constructor ABORTS (abortOnMismatch) on an absent map -> would crash system_server (AMS
+    // AppProfiler reads this). Probe first and degrade gracefully (no GPU-mem accounting) instead.
+    if (access(kBpfGpuMemTotalMap, F_OK) != 0) {
+        return false;
+    }
     // Use the read-only wrapper BpfMapRO to properly retrieve the read-only map.
     auto map = bpf::BpfMapRO<uint64_t, uint64_t>(kBpfGpuMemTotalMap);
     if (!map.isValid()) {
@@ -469,6 +476,13 @@ bool ReadProcessGpuUsageKb([[maybe_unused]] uint32_t pid, [[maybe_unused]] uint3
     // BPF Key [32-bits GPU ID | 32-bits PID]
     uint64_t kBpfKeyGpuUsage = ((uint64_t)gpu_id << 32) | pid;
 
+    // channel A17: gpu_mem_total_map is absent on this 4.9 kernel (no gpu_mem tracepoint -> gpuMem.o
+    // never loads). BpfMapRO(pathname) aborts on an absent map; probe first and report 0 usage
+    // gracefully so AMS AppProfiler's GPU-mem read doesn't crash system_server.
+    if (access(kBpfGpuMemTotalMap, F_OK) != 0) {
+        if (size) *size = 0;
+        return false;
+    }
     // Use the read-only wrapper BpfMapRO to properly retrieve the read-only map.
     auto map = bpf::BpfMapRO<uint64_t, uint64_t>(kBpfGpuMemTotalMap);
     if (!map.isValid()) {
